<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-888-388  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 888 388.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  Oct 25 1989 n118 p154(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mailshot Plus. (Software Review) (Digita International; Shortlist)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Gail.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digita International (products).andO;Product:   Mailshot Plus (Computer program).andO;Topic:     Mail PreparationSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   User verdict. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Mailshot PlusandM;Mailshots can be incredibly time consuming so this package from DigitaInternational -- which claims to be one of the most powerful on the market --could be the answer to the problem.andM;Unfortunately, there appeared to be no installation or loading program on thedisk.andP;  The manual maintains that installation instructions can be found inAppendix two.andP;  I only had one Appendix so I was none the wiser.andP;  But aftersearching through every file on the program disk I finally managed to loadMailshot and access the program.andM;As a label creator the package is pretty comprehensive.andP;  The display isWYSIWYG style -- the main menu appears vertically down the left-hand side ofthe screen whilst the labels are down the right.andP;  So if you want to changethe width and height of labels, or to centre or justify the layout of yourtext, then you can view the end product on screen.andM;One of the most powerful features of the program is its search facilities.andO;You can search for any line or any marked line through any set or subset oflabels.andP;  There's also a function for detecting any duplicate labels.andP;  Labelscan be sorted into alphabetical order via the initial of the first entry --or if you've addressed everyone as Ms then you can choose to mark a line ofyour label using a function key and then sort by that marked line.andM;Other functions include access to DOS command lines through the OS functionin the Main Menu.andP;  Files can be imported and exported using ASCII format.andO;Another handy extra allows you to create a column tabulated summary.andO;</TEXT></DOC>